Cameroon Banks to Loan Cotton Company Funding for 2011 Harvest

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-03-09T16:53:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/cameroon-banks-to-loan-cotton-company-funding-for-2011-harvest.html
Four banks in  Cameroon  will lend 6.5
billion  CFA francs  ($13.7 million) to the Cotton Development
Corp. to pay farmers and fund fertilizer and pesticides,
according to a statement from the company.  Afriland First Bank  will lend 2 billion francs, Societe
Generale SA’s unit will give 2 billion francs, Banque
Internationale du Cameroun pour l’Epargne et le Credit will lend
1.5 billion francs and Commercial Bank Cameroon will give 1
billion francs, said Iya Mohamed, general manager of the cotton
corporation, in a statement handed to reporters today in
Yaounde, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 